Step 1 — Program Registers :

Software writes: SRC_ADDR, DST_ADDR & LENGTH

Example: SRC_ADDR = 0, DST_ADDR = 16 & LENGTH   = 8

Meaning: Copy 8 words from mem[0:7] to mem[16:23]

Step 2 — Start Transfer :

Software writes: CTRL.START = 1

FSM transitions: IDLE -> READ

Step 3 — READ State

Controller reads source SRAM data & stores into internal buffer

Example:

data_buffer <= mem[src_ptr]
Step 4 — WRITE State

Controller:

writes buffered data to destination

Example:

mem[dst_ptr] <= data_buffer

Then increments:

source pointer
destination pointer
transfer counter

Step 5 — DONE State

When transfer completes:

done = 1
irq  = 1

Software notified through interrupt.

Step 6 — IRQ Clear

Software writes:

IRQ_CLEAR = 1

Controller:

clears interrupt
returns FSM to IDLE

FSM States
State	Description
IDLE	Wait for START
READ	Read source data
WRITE	Write destination data
DONE	Transfer completed
ERROR	Illegal configuration
Error Conditions

Controller enters ERROR state when:

LENGTH = 0
source address out of range
destination address out of range
transfer exceeds SRAM boundary
